{"version":2.92,"type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.DialogueTreeExt","translation":{"x":-7283.0,"y":-6209.0},"zoomFactor":0.9813862,"nodes":[{"statement":{"_text":"All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given to us. I can provide guidance in your journey.","_meta":"Trainer_Berg_Sage_01"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5670.0,"y":5205.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"2"},{"availableChoices":[{"statement":{"_text":"I want to train with you.","_meta":"Merchant_Generic_Train_01"}},{"statement":{"_text":"I\u2019d like to talk.","_meta":"Merchant_Generic_Talk_01"}}],"_position":{"x":5700.0,"y":5355.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.MultipleChoiceNodeExt","$id":"4"},{"_action":{"Trainer":{"_name":"myTrainer","_targetVariableID":"763c1c0e-163c-4e01-9626-9cd0a32f0fa6"},"PlayerCharacter":{"_name":"gInstigator","_targetVariableID":"78d35a0e-9529-4014-860f-d63311e1cef1"},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Actions.TrainDialogueAction"},"_position":{"x":5535.0,"y":5610.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.ActionNode","$id":"10"},{"statement":{"_text":"What is it you wish to talk about?","_meta":"Basic_Rune_Book_00"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5835.0,"y":5580.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"14"},{"availableChoices":[{"statement":{"_text":"Can you teach me the basics of rune combination?","_meta":"Player_Basic_Rune_Book_a_01"}},{"statement":{"_text":"Can you teach me how to do advanced rune combinations?","_meta":"Player_Advanced_Rune_Book_a_01"}},{"statement":{"_text":"I\u2019m having trouble understanding how to make combinations, is there a shortcut you can teach me?","_meta":"Player_Advanced_Rune_Book_a_05"}},{"statement":{"_text":"Farewell.","_meta":"Merchant_Generic_Farewell_01"}}],"_position":{"x":5895.0,"y":5715.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.MultipleChoiceNodeExt","$id":"16"},{"statement":{"_text":"Runes are a highly flexible form of magic, but require experimentation to get the most out of. For beginners, a Lexicon is required to be held in the caster\u2019s off-hand, as each rune has a multitude of meanings depending on their context.","_meta":"Basic_Rune_Book_01"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5415.0,"y":5880.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"26"},{"statement":{"_text":"Runes typically linger upon the caster after they are invoked. In order to create a tangible effect, one must cast a combination of runes in a set order. If a combination is not valid, nothing will happen.","_meta":"Basic_Rune_Book_02"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5340.0,"y":5985.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"28"},{"statement":{"_text":"A simple spell is the Runic Blade, which forms a sword of pure mana that is naturally imbued with the power of Light. First, you must cast the Shim Rune, followed by the Egoth rune. Dropping the weapon will cause it to return to nothingness.","_meta":"Basic_Rune_Book_03"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5340.0,"y":6090.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"30"},{"statement":{"_text":"For those who are part of a prominent family that has earned my trust, like the Aberdeens and the Sutherlands, I can offer to teach you how to Internalize the Lexicon so that you no longer need one in order to cast rune spells.","_meta":"Basic_Rune_Book_04"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5370.0,"y":6195.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"32"},{"_position":{"x":5520.0,"y":6300.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.FinishNode","$id":"34"},{"_condition":{"character":{"_name":"gInstigator","_targetVariableID":"78d35a0e-9529-4014-860f-d63311e1cef1"},"skill":{"_value":1},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Conditions.Condition_KnowSkill"},"_position":{"x":6105.0,"y":6000.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.ConditionNode","$id":"35"},{"statement":{"_text":"Very well, now that you understand the fundamentals of Advanced Runes, I can teach you how to put them into practice. Some rune combinations are effective only after another rune combination has been activated.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_01"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5790.0,"y":6150.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"39"},{"statement":{"_text":"For example, once you have cast a Runic Trap spell and it lies ready on the floor, perform \u201cShim\u201d, then \u201cShim\u201d again to create a Runic Blast that will detonate around you, harming nearby foes, but not yourself.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_02"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5775.0,"y":6255.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"41"},{"statement":{"_text":"It\u2019s a useful spell if your enemy evades your trap and is bearing down on you. Very few foes expect such a trick from a mage. Many more combinations like this exist with other Runic spells, and only through thoughtful experimentation can one reveal them.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_03"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":5715.0,"y":6390.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"43"},{"_position":{"x":6210.0,"y":6555.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.FinishNode","$id":"45"},{"statement":{"_text":"I would if I could, but to actually perform an advanced rune spell, you will need to learn the fundamental theory of advanced runes. Once I have taught them to you, ask me again and I can teach you one of those combinations.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_04"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":6330.0,"y":6195.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"46"},{"_condition":{"QuestEventRef":{"m_eventUID":"l237r5lo5U21PTGuyDZvcg"},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Conditions.Condition_QuestEventOccured"},"_position":{"x":6930.0,"y":6030.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.ConditionNode","$id":"48"},{"statement":{"_text":"Listen well, then. Most experienced runic mages come to the conclusion that each of the four known runes in Aurai fall under certain broad categories, and use this to more easily build runic combinations. ","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_08"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":6705.0,"y":6285.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"51"},{"statement":{"_text":"While crude and incorrect in some edge cases, it is a valid approach. These broad categories by rune are: Dez means \u201cDefense\u201d, Shim means \u201cOffense\u201d, Egoth stands for \u201cSelf\u201d and Fal means \u201cHidden\u201d. If you are still a beginner to whom this is new information, it may be helpful.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_09"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":6690.0,"y":6420.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"53"},{"statement":{"_text":"Never forget that the order in which you cast these runes is important. You may find the proper combination of runes, but fail to cast a spell because you cast the runes in the wrong order.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_10"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":6660.0,"y":6555.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"55"},{"_position":{"x":6825.0,"y":6705.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.FinishNode","$id":"57"},{"statement":{"_text":"Ahh...It goes against my every teaching, but I suppose I can teach you one dirty little trick, on one of two conditions. I crave Diad\u00e8me de Gibier. It\u2019s been years since I\u2019ve had a bite of that exquisite desert dish...","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_06"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":7320.0,"y":6225.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"58"},{"statement":{"_text":"Bring me some Diad\u00e8me de Gibier and I\u2019ll teach you that little trick. Or, I suppose if the Collective owes you a Tribal Favor, I can make an exception to my rules and teach you.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_07"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":7365.0,"y":6345.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"60"},{"availableChoices":[{"statement":{"_text":"I have some Diad\u00e8me de Gibier for you. Teach me that trick!","_meta":"Player_Advanced_Rune_Book_a_07"},"condition":{"character":{"_name":"gInstigator","_targetVariableID":"78d35a0e-9529-4014-860f-d63311e1cef1"},"item":{"_value":{"m_itemID":4100470}},"minAmount":{"_value":1},"itemMustBeEquiped":{},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Conditions.Condition_OwnsItem"}},{"statement":{"_text":"I\u2019m calling in a Tribal Favor. Teach me, please.","_meta":"Player_Trainer_Micro_Generic_a_01"},"condition":{"character":{"_name":"gInstigator","_targetVariableID":"78d35a0e-9529-4014-860f-d63311e1cef1"},"item":{"_value":{"m_itemID":5600050}},"minAmount":{"_value":1},"itemMustBeEquiped":{},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Conditions.Condition_OwnsItem"}},{"statement":{"_text":"Farewell.","_meta":"Merchant_Generic_Farewell_01"}}],"_position":{"x":7515.0,"y":6480.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.MultipleChoiceNodeExt","$id":"62"},{"_action":{"actions":[{"fromCharacter":{"_name":"gInstigator","_targetVariableID":"78d35a0e-9529-4014-860f-d63311e1cef1"},"Items":[{"_value":{"m_itemID":4100470}}],"Amount":[{"_value":1}],"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Actions.RemoveItem"},{"QuestEventRef":{"m_eventUID":"l237r5lo5U21PTGuyDZvcg"},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Actions.SendQuestEvent"}],"$type":"NodeCanvas.Framework.ActionList"},"_position":{"x":7155.0,"y":6690.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.ActionNode","$id":"82"},{"statement":{"_text":"Ahhh, Diad\u00e8me de Gibier! It\u2019s been so incredibly long! Alright, you\u2019ve twisted my arm.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_11"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":7065.0,"y":6810.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"94"},{"_targetNode":{"$ref":"51"},"_position":{"x":7230.0,"y":6930.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.GoToNode","$id":"96"},{"_action":{"actions":[{"fromCharacter":{"_name":"gInstigator","_targetVariableID":"78d35a0e-9529-4014-860f-d63311e1cef1"},"Items":[{"_value":{"m_itemID":5600050}}],"Amount":[{"_value":1}],"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Actions.RemoveItem"},{"QuestEventRef":{"m_eventUID":"l237r5lo5U21PTGuyDZvcg"},"$type":"NodeCanvas.Tasks.Actions.SendQuestEvent"}],"$type":"NodeCanvas.Framework.ActionList"},"_position":{"x":7560.0,"y":6690.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.ActionNode","$id":"97"},{"statement":{"_text":"Very well, for the sake of our Tribes, I will teach you.","_meta":"Advanced_Rune_Book_12"},"_actorName":"name_trainer_sagetrainer_01 ","_actorParameterID":"8b9c0625-6c3d-4588-ae4e-76f04f07aeb3","_position":{"x":7515.0,"y":6825.0},"$type":"NodeCanvas.DialogueTrees.StatementNodeExt","$id":"109"},{"_targetNode":{"$ref":"51"},"_position":{"x":7620.0,"y":6